        <div id="featureMain">
          <h5>Feature</h5>
          <ul><li><h5>Learn More<br/></h5>Would you like to learn more about Islam in China? See the subject entries in <em><a href="http://www.oxfordislamicstudies.com/article/opr/t236/e0383#e0383-s5" target="_blank" title="The Oxford Encyclopedia of the Islamic World">The Oxford Encyclopedia of the Islamic World</a> </em>and <em><a href="http://www.oxfordislamicstudies.com/article/opr/t355/e0234?_hi=0&amp;_pos=2#" target="_blank" title="The Oxford Encyclopedia of Islam and Women">The Oxford Encyclopedia of Islam and Women</a>.</em></li><li><h5>Subject Entries</h5>New subject entries include additions to our spotlights on <a href="http://www.oxfordislamicstudies.com/ReferenceWorks/guide_24.html" target="_blank">Islam, Gender, and Sexuality</a> (Samar Habib, editor), Islamic Philosophy and Philosophers (Ayman Shihadeh, editor), <a href="http://www.oxfordislamicstudies.com/ReferenceWorks/guide_15.html" target="_blank" title="Islam in Southeast Asia">Islam in Southeast Asia</a> (Imtiyaz Yusuf, editor), <a href="http://www.oxfordislamicstudies.com/ReferenceWorks/guide_20.html" target="_blank" title="Islam in Andalusia">Islam in Andalusia</a> (Brian Catlos, editor) and the <a href="http://www.oxfordislamicstudies.com/ReferenceWorks/guide_21.html" target="_blank" title="Encyclopedia of Islamic Bioethics">Encyclopedia of Islamic Bioethics</a> (Ayman Shabana, editor). See the full list <a href="http://www.oxfordislamicstudies.com/Public/whats_new.html">here</a>.</li><li><h5>Learning Resources</h5>A new <a href="http://www.oxfordislamicstudies.com/lessonplan_26.html">lesson plan</a> on Progressive Islam by Adis Duderija.</li></ul>
                                                                                                                                                                                                         
<font size="3">                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       <ul><li><h5>Interviews<br/></h5>Continuing   our ongoing interview series, Mobashra Tazamal (The Bridge Institute)   talks to author Samira Ahmed about her bestselling novel <em>Love, Hate &amp; Other Filters</em>   (Soho Press), in which Muslim teenager Maya Aziz struggles to navigate   her own path in life  while confronting a wave of Islamophobia in the   wake of a terrorist  attack. <a href="http://www.oxfordislamicstudies.com/interview_13.html">Read more</a></li></ul>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           <ul><li><h5>What Everyone Needs to Know about Islam, Second Edition<br/></h5>    Here is a fast, centralized path to John Esposito's updated guide to   Muslim faith, customs, and political beliefs, based on questions   Esposito has been asked by a diverse range of audiences. <a href="http://www.oxfordislamicstudies.com/Public/book_wenkai.html">Read more</a></li></ul></font>
        </div>
